properties.headline: Blizzard Warning issued January 1 at 8:50AM AKST until January 1 at 4:00PM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blizzard conditions occurring. Near zero visibility in
snow and blowing snow. Additional snow accumulations of up to 4
inches. Southwest winds gusting 25 to 40 mph.

* WHERE...Along the northern shore of Kachemak Bay, including
Homer and the Homer Bluff.

* WHEN...Until 4 PM AKST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Plan for hazardous travel conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow and winds will gradually diminish
through the afternoon hours, leading to improved visibilities.
properties.instruction:
A Blizzard Warning means severe winter weather conditions are
expected or occurring. Falling and blowing snow with strong winds
and poor visibilities are likely. This will lead to whiteout
conditions, making travel very hazardous. If you must travel,
have a winter survival kit with you.If you get stranded, stay
with your vehicle.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: BLIZZARD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM AKST THIS AFTERNOON
